#Approach:

Search Insert Position – Lower Bound Concept

Is problem me hume target ka position find karna hota hai.
Agar target array me exist karta hai to uska index return karna hai,
warna jis position par wo insert hoga sorted order maintain rakhne ke liye,
wo index return karna hai.

Ye exactly Lower Bound hota hai.

Lower Bound ka matlab:
First index jahan value >= target ho.

Binary search use karte hain:
Agar nums[mid] >= target:
    ho sakta hai ye answer ho, isliye ans = mid store karte hain
    aur left side me search karte hain (high = mid - 1)
Else:
    target right side me hoga (low = mid + 1)

Loop ke baad ans hi lower bound hota hai.

Time Complexity: O(log n)

Upper Bound Concept

Upper Bound ka matlab:
First index jahan value > target ho.

Binary search me:
Agar nums[mid] > target:
    ye possible answer hai
    ans = mid
    high = mid - 1
Else:
    low = mid + 1

Lower Bound → first >= target
Upper Bound → first > target

Memory Trick:
LB = >= target
UB = > target

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] nums, int target) {
        //This is Lower Bound only
        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;
        int ans = nums.length;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;

            if(nums[mid] >= target){
                ans = mid;
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
